In this statement, President Obama thanks the National Commission on Fiscal Responsibility and Reform for their work in highlighting the challenge of the national debt. He emphasizes the need for strong economic growth and the necessity of making difficult choices to curb the debt. The President acknowledges that both Democrats and Republicans need to find common ground and work together to address this challenge. He also mentions that he will study the Commission's proposals and work on reducing the deficit by slowing healthcare costs, freezing spending, and paying for priorities. The President calls for honest conversation and cooperation in order to lift the burden of debt from future generations.